    "Leverage Python 3.12+ features, such as improved type hinting and PEP 604 for better code organization"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "```python\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, BackgroundTasks\napp = FastAPI()\n@app.post('/train/model')\nasync def train_model(data: ModelInput):\n    background_task = BackgroundTasks.run_in_background(train_function, data)\nn    return {'status': 'Model training initiated'}n\ndef train_function(data: ModelInput):\n    # Training code goes here...\n```"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for the use of BackgroundTasks",
    "FastAPI version 0.74.0 or later is recommended for better compatibility with Python 3.12+ features"
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "BackgroundTasks may not be suitable for very long-running tasks as they don't have a guarantee of completion",
